  <!-- The Scoreboard Lists widget takes care of fancy statistics that are shown in the scoreboard state. 
    They lists are quite easy to handle. With the help of the <list> tag you specify an empty
    list container which you can position and size with the help of the tags <x>, <y>, <width>
    and <entrycount>. You can give your list a title with the help of the <title>-tag and finetune
    its horizontal position with the help of <titleoffsetx>.
    Now it's time to fill this empty box with content. At the moment the <content> tag can be
    one of those:
    
     Only for trackmania:
      - 'DediRecs' : Dedimania records     
    
     For Time based Modes in Shootmania / Trackmania:
      - 'LocalRecs': local records
      - 'MostRecs'   : players that have the most records on your server
      
     Generall Lists:
      - 'TopRanks' : top ranked players in Time Modes
      - 'AllPoints' : top ranked players in Point Modes (only shootmania)
      - 'TopPlaytime': players that spent the most time on your server
      - 'TopWinners' : most victorius players
      - 'TopDons' : list the top donators
            
     Only for Shootmania:
      - 'MostHits': players with most hits
      - 'MostSurvivals': players with most survivals
      - 'MostCaptures': players with most captures
      - 'MostRespawns': players with most respawns
      - 'MostDeaths': players with most deaths
      - 'MostNearMisses': players with most near misses   
      - 'WeeklyPoints': Best Players Weekly (Only in Point modes, depency plugin.timedrank.php)           
      - 'MonthlyPoints': Best Players Monthly (Only in Point modes, depency plugin.timedrank.php)                  
    If you configured a list right, it will always be shown when the scoreboard pops up -->
     
